June 30 at 3:17 PM ·

We’re very excited to say that our grab-and-go meals program will be continuing throughout the summer!

Meals are available between 4:30-5:30 PM every Monday through Friday at both our Brockton and Taunton Clubhouses. Grab & Go dinners are available for any and ALL youth ages 0-18, not just BGCMS Club members!

Children DO NOT need to be present at pick-up but we ask that parents please take only one meal per child in their household.

#BGCMetroSouth #GreatFutures

Build A Life MA
May 28 at 1:22 PM ·

Happy 20% Day! Today we celebrate the thousands of girls enrolled in construction-related programs in CTE High Schools across MA.

Thanks to the hard work of the leaders and partners of the Mass Girls in Trades (MAGIT) initiative, the percentage of girls in construction-related programs has reached 19.7%, essentially meeting our goal of 20% by 2020.
#20Percentby2020 #TheFutureisFemale

Given the evolving data regarding cases of COVID-19, and out of an abundance of caution for the health and safety of children and school staff, the Governor has ordered a three-week suspension of school operations for educational purposes at all public and private elementary and secondary (K-12) schools in the Commonwealth continuing until Tuesday, April 7, 2020.

We will continue to keep you apprised of any developments as they occur.

In addition, Caleigh Martin's 1st place pin design will be traded at the national conference in May, and Julia Cullinane was elected to state office where she will be serving as BPA State Secretary! Way to go team 🎉
